                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3n010d71/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(center)\">In the Synod of <placeName>New York</placeName>:</p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\">At <placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>Oct. 17<hi rend=\"sup\"\n                        >th</hi>. 1850</date>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">The Committee to whom had been referred<lb/> certain papers\n                communicated by the <persName>Revd. Isaac<lb/> Leeser</persName>, from various\n                sources, noticing the Ad-<lb/>dres to the Jews by the Synod last year, made<lb/> a\n                report which was adopted, as follows, viz</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">“Whereas the documents addressed to the<lb/> Synod and referred to\n                this Committee are from<lb/> individual Israelites, unauthorized to speak<lb/> for\n                the Jewish Community within the bounds of<lb/> the Synod, therefore, Resolved that\n                the committee<lb/> cannot recommend to the Synod to make<lb/> any official reply to\n                the same.”</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Attest.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">John M Krebs</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(4)\">Stated Clerk.</p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3n010d71/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
